BFF. ♾️
We just talked Friday. I was telling about my event and how I wasn’t sure about getting that dress. Well, I got it. It worked out. We talked about your family, Jayden, my family. Keeping our peace & setting boundaries with folks. The future. We talked for 2 hours. 

You were there for everyone around you. You were there for me whenever & however you could be. 

We walked to school together, everyday as kids when I lived in Cleveland Heights. 

Every secret. Every pain. Every milestone. Every dream. You knew about it. You watched from afar. You supported and celebrated it. We encourage each other. 

You took care of everyone around you. Asked for nothing in return. You spoke your mind. You were a protector. 

This makes no sense. None. We were just joking about Jayden’s prom being years from now. 

Know that you were wise beyond your years, beautiful and rare. There will never be another friend like you in my life. My Bestie — no matter how far the distance. You didn’t like pictures. So glad I got you to take this one on your bday back in 2016. 

I love you always…🤍

Life lately. 🤍

I used to be co-dependent and didn’t know it. Toxic relationships and friendships had me doubting my value.  It wasn’t until I really, surrendered my life to Christ and realized even though I had been a believer most of my life, deep down, I had an issue trusting God. 

The pain of my failed marriage almost took me out, y’all. Foreal. Those who know, know. I kept myself busy, tried to be as focused and as strong as could be, grieved when I needed to and did a lot of self reflection. I still am healing.

Have you ever hoped & prayed for something so badly that you just knew it was going to happen? That by your sheer might, energy, and effort it HAD to happen? Faith right!? Just have faith like a mustard seed right? Then put the work in, Faith + works right? Well, two can only walk together if they agree.

I wrestled reconciling the outcome of my decision making, my desires and the faith I put into the beautiful picture God showed me of what my marriage could have been.

When I came to terms with the truth I realized I was not whole going into the that relationship in the first place. I was on my way to owning my identity but I was not there yet. Potentially, had I been further along in my personal development journey I would have made different decisions.

Two broken peices don’t make a whole piece, they only have the potential to cut each other with their sharp edges when trying to bind together. When binding two broken pieces the best case scenario is  for both pieces to have the glue of the Holy Spirit on them as a cushion and a strong adhesive, binding them into place.

With my reset, my new beginning, I’m allowing God to make me a whole porcelain dish, ornate and polished ready to be placed place it in its proper position, among other fine China, preserving its value and used for its appropriate purpose. 

I’m glad God causes all things to work together for our good. I am also glad that I saw how deeply I could love.

Now that I can honestly say I’m happy alone, I’m only open to what God will bring into my life that will add to that happiness. It’s giving “ER” season.. LOL 

#freelyc #relationships #selflove #healing

Filled with so much gratitude. God is truly more than able. I can testify. He is a healer of broken hearts. He is a provider and protector.

Today for “Throwback Thursday,” throwback all of the drama, stress and pain you have held on to this year and sprint towards this new year in faith that God is able. He is able to provide, able to heal, able to change your circumstances, whatever they maybe.

I almost lost my faith during these last two years of my life. I was devastated that the vision I had for my life, did not materialize as I envisioned to say the least. I questioned my judgement, I questioned God’s character, I questioned everything. I’m glad God doesn’t give up easily. He brought community around me to remind me of the truth. He meet me in the hard places of my deep sadness.

People don’t often want to share their struggle on here but I think there is more power in sharing the hard times then only sharing the victories. 

God is really is able to change any circumstance around if we let him. Just keep the faith, do the work and wait on him. 

“Therefore we also, since we are surrounded by so great a cloud of witnesses, let us lay aside every weight, and the sin which so easily ensnares us, and let us run with endurance the race that is set before us, looking unto Jesus, the author and finisher of our faith, who for the joy that was set before Him endured the cross, despising the shame, and has sat down at the right hand of the throne of God.“
‭‭Hebrews‬ ‭12‬:‭1‬-‭2‬ ‭NKJV‬‬
